replies.body:
I really don't want to be rude, but AP Galio's Q literally does enough damage to one shot superminions, and it doesn't even take any crazy build, just regular RoA mage - how did it even make it outside of PBE? Isn't anyone monitoring new content ATM? I get that this is the busiest time of year for you Rioters, but really, AP Galio is your biggest slip in a long, long time.

I just hope you will find time for a hotfix. At __VERY__ least, minion damage needs to be capped, one shoting superminions just should not happen, much less be a standard for any champion.
{{sticker:katarina-love}}

Can you please make {{item:3050}} interact with AP again somehow? One of the coolest things about pre-rework Zekes was that it gave both 50% crit chance AND a 30% bonus to ability power thus the item was still viable in more...obscure lanes

{{champion:63}} and {{champion:1}} 
{{champion:267}}  and {{champion:89}} 
{{champion:25}}  and {{champion:90}}  
{{champion:82}}  and {{champion:48}} 
are all some more unconventional AP focused lanes me and my friends enjoyed trying but with the new update to Zekes its interaction with ability power was lost. It would be nice if more support itemization and effects benefited a wider pool of champions rather than just being geared for Right clickers (The already have Stoneborn Pact and{{item:3504}} which is directly more effective with AS) .

So can you guys look into allowing the "Burn" part apply on magic damage or maybe giving its burn a AP ratio too?
thanks in advance
